Package: rschrodinger
Title: Fast Data Bridge Between Schrodinger and R
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: 
    person("Jixing", "Liu", , "jixing.liu@example.com", role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"))
Description: Read Maestro (.mae/.maegz) files natively in R without
    requiring a Schrodinger installation. Optionally bridge to
    Schrodinger's Python API for protein-ligand interaction analysis
    and job monitoring via sandboxed subprocess calls.
Depends: R (>= 4.1.0)
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 7.3.3
Suggests: 
    testthat (>= 3.0.0)
Config/testthat/edition: 3
Imports: 
    cli,
    jsonlite,
    processx,
    rlang,
    tibble,
    withr
